==== 信息和电子邮件自由 ====
戈夫一直是被反复批评试图逃避《{{le|英国信息自由法|Freedom of Information Act 2000}}》的某些规定的关键人物。批评包括戈夫使用各种私人电子邮件帐户来发送涉嫌与他的部门职责有关的电子邮件。这些指控表明，戈夫和他的顾问们相信他们可以避免他们的通信受信息自由的要求，因为他们认为他们的私人电子邮件帐户不受信息自由法案的约束。2011年9月，[[金融時報_(英國)|金融时报]]报道说，戈夫使用了一个未公开的私人电子邮件帐户“Mrs Blurt”，与顾问讨论政府的业务。<ref>{{cite news |last=Ensor |first=Josie |url= http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/8775646/Michael-Gove-faces-questions-over-use-of-private-email.html |title=Michael Gove faces questions over use of private email |trans_title=戈夫面临使用私人电子邮件的问题 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |accessdate=2012-08-25 |date=2011-09-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Vasagar |first=Jeevan |url= https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2012/mar/02/michael-gove-email-private-account |newspaper=The Guardian |title=Michael Gove aides accused of deleting government correspondence |trans_title=戈夫的助理被指控删除政府信件 | date=2012-03-02|accessdate=2012-03-02}}</ref>2012年3月，英国信息专员裁定，由于金融时报要求的电子邮件包含公共信息，它们可能是信息自由请求的主体，所以命令披露该文件的信息。<ref>{{cite press release |last=Smith |first=Graham |title=Decision Notice |trans_title=决定通知 |url=http://www.ico.gov.uk/news/latest_news/2012/~/media/documents/decisionnotices/2012/fs_50422276.ashx |publisher=Information Commissioner's Office |date=2012-03-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120306035417/http://www.ico.gov.uk/news/latest_news/2012/~/media/documents/decisionnotices/2012/fs_50422276.ashx |archivedate=2012-03-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-17235168 |title=Michael Gove loses 'private email' battle |trans_title=戈夫在“私人电子邮件”的战斗中失败 |publisher=BBC News |date=2012-03-02}}</ref>戈夫还建议停止使用私人电子邮件帐户进行政府业务的做法。戈夫对信息专员的裁决提出异议，然后前往法庭，偿还纳税人支付的12540英镑的法律咨询费，<ref>{{Cite news |last= McSmith |first= Andy |date= 2012-10-26 |title= Tony Blair may be an admirer of Ukrainian mills, but not on the basis of British ones he's visited |trans_title=托尼·布莱尔可能是乌克兰农庄的崇拜者，但不是因为他见过的英国人 |url= http://www.independent.co.uk/voices/comment/tony-blair-may-be-an-admirer-of-ukrainian-mills-but-not-on-the-basis-of-british-ones-hes-visited-8228721.html |newspaper= [[The_Independent|The Independent]] |accessdate= 2014-02-23 }}</ref>但上诉被撤回。<ref>{{cite news |last=Vasagar |first=Jeevan |title=Michael Gove appeals against ruling on misuse of email |trans_title=迈克尔·戈维呼吁反对滥用电子邮件的裁决 |url= https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2012/mar/29/michael-gove-appeal-against-email-ruling |newspaper=The Guardian |date=2012-03-29}}</ref>

=== 保守党领袖候选人（2016年） ===
在[[戴维·卡梅伦|戴维·卡梅伦]]宣布他打算辞去首相之后，他的继任者可能在9月就职，戈夫还不是候选人，过去他曾说过没有兴趣成为首相。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/05/06/michael-gove-rules-out-running-for-tory-leader-and-says-his-frie/ |title=Michael Gove rules out running for Tory leader and says his friendship with David Cameron will survive the referendum |trans_title=迈克尔·戈夫不会参加为保守党领袖选举，并说他与戴维·卡梅伦的友谊将在公投继续保持 |access-date=2016-06-30}}</ref>相反，他被认为是强大的有影响力的首相候选人[[鲍里斯·约翰逊|鲍里斯·约翰逊]]的支持者。在一个让大多数政治分析家感到惊讶的举动中，戈夫于2016年6月30日撤回了对约翰逊的支持，并宣布自己是[[2016年英國保守黨黨魁選舉|2016年英國保守黨黨魁選舉]]的候选人，而事先约翰逊没有接到没有任何通知。随后，约翰逊退出。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-36672591 |title=Boris Johnson rules himself out of Conservative leader race |trans_title=鲍里斯·约翰逊退出保守党领袖选自保 |access-date=2016-06-30 |archive-date=2016-07-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701043501/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-36672591 |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[每日电讯报|每日电讯报]]指出，戈夫破坏约翰逊成为领袖愿望的行动堪称了“五十年一遇的最壮观的政治暗杀”，<ref>{{cite web|last1=Swinford|first1=Steven|last2=Hope|first2=Christopher|last3=Dominiczak|first3=Peter|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/06/30/boris-johnsons-allies-accuse-michael-gove-of-systematic-and-calc/|title=Boris Johnson's allies accuse Michael Gove of 'systematic and calculated plot' to destroy his leadership hopes|trans_title=鲍里斯·约翰逊的盟友指责迈克尔·戈夫的“系统和精确的图谋”，摧毁约翰逊的领袖梦|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=2016-06-30|accessdate=2016-07-05|archive-date=2016-06-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160630224842/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/06/30/boris-johnsons-allies-accuse-michael-gove-of-systematic-and-calc/|dead-url=no}}</ref>而卫报将其称为“马基雅维利式的举动”。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mason|first1=Rowena|last2=Stewart|first2=Heather|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/jun/30/goves-thunderbolt-boris-johnson-tory-morning|title=Gove's thunderbolt and Boris's breaking point: a shocking Tory morning|trans_title=戈夫的雷霆一击和约翰逊的断点：一个令人震惊的托利早晨 |work=The Guardian|date=2015-06-30|accessdate=2016-07-05}}</ref>

戈夫说：“我想帮助建立一个团队支持鲍里斯·约翰逊，使一个支持脱欧的政治家可以带领我们走向一个更美好的未来。但是，我不情愿地得出结论，鲍里斯不能完成领导或建立未来团队的任务。因此，我决定把我的名字推向领导层。关于国家现在将采取的道路，我想要有一个公开和积极的辩论。无论辩论的结果如何，我将尊重。在接下来的几天里，我将为英国制定我的计划，我希望能够提供团结和变革。”<ref>{{cite news |last=Cowburn |first=Ashley |date=2016-06-30 |title=Michael Gove's statement on running for Tory leadership against Boris Johnson |trans_title=迈克尔·戈夫关于鲍里斯·约翰逊领袖选举运动的声明 |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/michael-goves-statement-on-running-for-tory-leadership-against-boris-johnson-read-it-in-full-a7110596.html |newspaper=The Independent |location=London |access-date=2016-06-30 }}</ref>

2016年7月5日，戈夫在保守党（英国）领导大选中排名第三，2016年落后于[[特蕾莎·梅|特蕾莎·梅]]和[[安德烈婭·利德索姆|安德利娅·利德索姆]];后者获得了鲍里斯·约翰逊的认可。一些政治分析家预测，如果戈夫在第一轮投票中无法击败利德索姆，他可能会退出竞争。<ref>{{cite news |last=Wilkinson |first=Michael |date=2016-07-05 |title=Conservative leadership election: Theresa May surges ahead as Tory MPs suggest Michael Gove could quit the race |trans_title=保守党领袖选举：特蕾莎·梅可能继续前进，因为托利议员们建议迈克尔·戈夫可以退出比赛了 |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/07/05/boris-johnson-backs-andrea-leadsom-tory-mps-vote-leadership-race/ |newspaper=The Telegraph |location=London |access-date=2016-07-05 }}</ref>当天晚些时候，宣布特蕾莎·梅赢得了第一轮投票，得到165人的支持，而[[安德烈婭·利德索姆|安德利娅·利德索姆]]获得了66票，戈夫以48票列第三。<ref name=autogenerated1 />

戈夫在第二轮投票中被淘汰了，只得46票，而梅得199票，利德索姆84票。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.com/news/live/uk-politics-36570120 |title=Michael Gove knocked out of Conservative leadership ballot |trans_title=迈克尔·戈夫在保守党领袖选举投票后出局 |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2016-07-07 |website=BBC |publisher=BBC |access-date=2016-07-07}}</ref>他随后告诉媒体，他“自然失望”，并把他的两个对手描述为“强大的政治家”，欢迎下一位首相将是女性的事实。他还鼓励“文明，包容，积极和乐观的辩论”。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-36737426 |title=Theresa May v Andrea Leadsom to be next prime minister |trans_title=梅与利德索姆的首相之战 |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2016-07-07 |website=BBC |publisher=BBC |access-date=2016-07-07}}</ref>

=== 采访特朗普 ===
作为《泰晤士报》的专栏作家，戈夫于2017年1月对[[唐纳德·特朗普|唐纳德·特朗普]]进行了美国大选后第一次英国人对其的采访，同时还有来自《图片报》的{{le|凯·德克曼|Kai Diekmann}}，<ref>{{cite news|last1=Gove|first1=Michael|title=Full transcript of interview with Donald Trump|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/full-transcript-of-interview-with-donald-trump-5d39sr09d|work=The Times|date=2017-01-16|accessdate=2017-01-18|subscription=y|archive-date=2019-04-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190429083114/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/full-transcript-of-interview-with-donald-trump-5d39sr09d|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Stewart|first1=Heather|title=Michael Gove secures first post-election UK interview with Trump|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2017/jan/15/michael-gove-uk-interview-tory-times|work=The Guardian|date=2017-01-15|accessdate=2017-01-18}}</ref>戈夫成为继[[奈杰尔·法拉奇|奈杰尔·法拉奇]]之后第二位与{{le|美国当选总统|President-elect of the United States}}会面的英国政治人物。<ref name="Sharman-Indy 2016a"/>尽管他更希望[[希拉里·克林顿|希拉里·克林顿]]能成为美国总统，<ref>{{cite av media|title=Newsnight|publisher=BBC News|date=2016-01-16|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/iplayer/episode/b08bgfpl/newsnight-16012017|accessdate=2017-01-18}}</ref>但他的采访和赞美被认为对于当选总统来说还是太过了，<ref>{{cite news|last1=Grace|first1=John|title=Michael Gove gorges on cheesy puff of Donald Trump interview|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2017/jan/16/michael-gove-cheesy-puff-donald-trump-interview|work=The Guardian|date=2017-01-16|accessdate=2017-01-18}}</ref>戈夫对特朗普[[拇指手勢|竖起大拇指]]的照片在社交媒体上引来一片嘲弄。<ref name="Demianyk-Huffpo 2017a">{{cite news|last1=Demianyk|first1=Graeme|title=Michael Gove Mocked For Donald Trump Thumbs Up Photograph|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/michael-gove-donald-trump_uk_587c08dee4b04a8bfe6aaca1|work=The Huffington Post|date=2017-01-16|accessdate=2017-01-18}}</ref>

在采访中，特朗普说，由于自己母亲来自苏格兰，他对英国很有好感。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hoyle|first1=Ben|title=‘I love Britain. My mother was crazy about the Queen’|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/edition/news/i-love-britain-my-mother-was-crazy-about-the-queen-twcc3wz22|work=The Times|date=2017-01-16|accessdate=2017-01-18|subscription=y}}</ref> 特朗普还表示支持[[英国脱离欧盟|英国脱离欧盟]]，描述投票脱欧“如此聪明”，并赞扬了英镑的贬值。<ref name="Osborne-Indy 2017a">{{cite news|last1=Osborne|first1=Samuel|title=10 important things Donald Trump said in his Times interview with Michael Gove|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/donald-trump-uk-interview-michael-gove-brexit-latest-news-times-important-reveals-us-president-elect-a7528996.html|work=The Independent|date=2017-01-16|accessdate=2017-01-18}}</ref>他还许诺美国会在英国脱欧后与英国达成自由贸易协议，但英国内阁大臣们已经警告特蕾莎·梅首相不要答应特朗普许诺的任何不会给英国和美国带来实际利益的贸易协议。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Coates|first1=Sam|title=Don't let Trump rush you into bad trade deal, May is warned|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/dont-let-trump-rush-you-into-bad-trade-deal-may-is-warned-z603zkgn6|work=The Times|date=2017-01-17|accessdate=2017-01-18|subscription=y}}</ref>

